  <prompt>
    Add a "Summarize a Document" entry to the existing `GetStartedCardsWidget` catalog
    so users discover the R5 chat-driven Summarize flow from the welcome-stage Context
    pane â€” not only via the `/summarize` slash command in the chat input. Clicking the
    card MUST open the file-upload dialog directly AND pre-fill the chat input with
    `/summarize ` (with trailing space) so the user can immediately type qualifiers and
    send, or send-with-empty-suffix to invoke the playbook. This is the discoverable
    parallel entry to the slash command per design.md Â§3.2 / spec FR-19+.

    This task is **REUSE-ONLY**: extend the existing `GetStartedCardsWidget` catalog
    array; do NOT introduce a parallel welcome system, do NOT add a new shell stage,
    do NOT add a new PaneEventBus channel. R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE.md Â§3.1) and ADR-030
    (4-channel close) bind. R5 also introduces NO new feature flag for this entry â€”
    visibility derives from `useShellStage()` returning the welcome stage per ADR-031.

    NO BFF code is changed by this task. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (confirm in
    notes). Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens + dark mode required per ADR-021. React 19
    only (ADR-022).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend engineer with Fluent UI v9 + React 19 expertise and prior R3/R4
    work on the SpaarkeAi Context pane. Familiar with `GetStartedCardsWidget`,
    `ContextPaneController`, the `widget_load` PaneEventBus event flow, the
    `useShellStage()` lifecycle hook (ADR-031), and the existing `/summarize` slash
    command + chat-input pre-fill pathway shipped in Phase 2.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The `GetStartedCardsWidget` catalog includes a "Summarize a Document" card visible
    on the welcome stage of the Context pane. Activating the card (click, Enter, or
    Space) does TWO things atomically: (1) opens the chat-pane file-upload dialog (the
    same dialog Phase 2 wired for the `/summarize` slash command and chat-pane paperclip
    affordance); (2) pre-fills the chat input with `/summarize ` (trailing space).
    Visibility is conditional on `useShellStage() === welcome` per ADR-031 â€” the card
    does NOT appear on non-welcome stages. Dark mode renders correctly (Fluent v9
    semantic tokens only; no hex / rgba literals). Existing 7-card layout + arrow-key
    navigation + tabbing + screen-reader announcement extend cleanly to the 8th card.
    `code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5. BFF publish-size delta
    = 0 MB (confirmed in task notes).
  </goal>

