  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice in Phase 2. The
      primary entry is the `/summarize` slash command in the chat input, paired with
      the paperclip upload affordance. Phase 3 task 041 adds the DISCOVERABLE parallel
      entry: a "Summarize a Document" card on the welcome-stage Context pane, alongside
      the existing 7 Get Started cards shipped in R3 (FR-18 / FR-19). The card lowers
      the discovery barrier for users who have not learned the slash command, and
      reinforces the chat-pane file-upload UX as the canonical Summarize entry point.

      The card differs from the existing R3 "Summarize Files" card (which targets the
      legacy LegalWorkspace `document-upload-wizard` Workspace widget path): the R5
      card targets the new chat-driven flow that uses `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`,
      `spaarke-session-files` index, and the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`. Two
      coexisting cards is intentional during R5 â€” Phase 3 / R6 may consolidate after
      operator feedback.
    </background>
